# App host — `infra/prod/docker-compose.app.yml` (**messaging-service** only: no MinIO, no RabbitMQ, no nginx in this file).
# TLS and HTTP are expected at a **load balancer** (e.g. ALB) in front of an autoscaling group; static SPA is usually hosted
# on S3/CloudFront or similar — not bind-mounted in compose.
# Copy to **`.env`** in repo root (or `docker compose --env-file <path>`). **Never** commit a real **`.env`**.
# Secrets: `RABBITMQ_PASS`, `JWT_SECRET`, `MONGODB_URI` (if it holds credentials), `AWS_*` — see `docs/prod-secrets.md`.
# S3 detail: `docs/prod-s3-and-r2.md`.
#
# Cross-host networking: `docs/prod-networking.md` — data plane runs `infra/prod/docker-compose.data.yml` (includes **RabbitMQ**).
# **Startup order:** (1) **Data** host: `docker compose -f infra/prod/docker-compose.data.yml up -d` (mongo, redis, minio, rabbitmq, …).
# (2) **App** host: set `MONGODB_URI`, `REDIS_URL`, `RABBITMQ_HOST` (or full `RABBITMQ_URL`), `S3_*` in `.env`, then
#   docker compose -f infra/prod/docker-compose.app.yml up -d --build
# (3) **Smoke (on app instance, direct):** `curl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:3001/v1/ready` — or your LB URL.
#
# Nginx + Certbot (Let’s Encrypt) are **not** in the default app compose. Sample configs for self-managed edge live under
# `infra/prod/nginx/`; see `docs/prod-acme-nginx.md` if you run nginx yourself.
#
# --- Data host (use private IP / DNS; must match the data **docker-compose** actually running) ---
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb://10.x.x.x:27017/messaging
# REDIS_URL=redis://10.x.x.x:6379
#
# RabbitMQ **on the data host** (5672 published) — use the same RABBITMQ_USER/PASS on both data and app `.env` files:
# RABBITMQ_USER=messaging
# RABBITMQ_PASS=change-me
# RABBITMQ_HOST=10.x.x.x
# Or override the full URL: RABBITMQ_URL=amqp://user:pass@10.x.x.x:5672
#
# Local dev (both compose files on one machine, **same** RABBITMQ_USER/PASS as data stack):
# RABBITMQ_HOST=host.docker.internal
#
# --- S3-compatible API (MinIO on data host, or R2 / AWS) ---
# S3_ENDPOINT=http://<data-private-ip>:9000
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=minio
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=minioadmin
# S3_BUCKET=messaging-media
# S3_REGION=us-east-1
# S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://...   # origin browsers use for presigned / public object paths
# S3_ANONYMOUS_GET_OBJECT=true
# Optional: S3_PRESIGN_ENDPOINT=...
#
# PUBLIC_APP_BASE_URL=https://ekko.biratbhattacharjee.com
#
# --- Observability (Prometheus on data host → scrape this app) ---
# `docker-compose.app.yml` publishes messaging-service on host **:3001**. If data + app run on the **same** host, remap one
# service in an **override** file (Grafana and messaging both default to 3001 on the host) — `infra/prod/monitoring/README.md`.
# ENABLE_PROMETHEUS_METRICS=true
#
# --- Web client (build in CI, deploy to static hosting) — see `apps/web-client/.env.example` (production) ---
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://.../v1
# VITE_S3_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=...
# VITE_S3_BUCKET=messaging-media
#   cd apps/web-client && npm run build
#
